''''Cattle station'''' is an Australian term for a large farm ([[ranch|Australian ranch]]), usually in the [[outback|outback]], whose main activity is the raising of [[cattle|cattle]].

It has a parallel term, [[Sheep station]] for those stations carrying sheep rather than cattle.  In most cases the stations are in a [[rangeland]] context on [[pastoral leases]].

The phrase is also in traditional [[Australian English|Australian English]] to denote something large and/or important.


